reviews.text: Warm and cozy atmosphere, but quality is far superior than many fine dining restaurants in HK

Casual little restaurant with beautifully prepared fresh pasta. Lobster linguine was beautifully cooked with just a hint of thyme. Dishes from other tables looked equally lovely. All very impressive from what looked like a one man band. Would recommend if you're looking for something different from the main seafront fare.
Nice place
